@Node "getFileWithPattern()" "asl/getFileWithPattern"

@{b}   NAME@{ub}
       getFileWithPattern() of @{"asl" Link "asl/asl()"} -- Get a file that matches the pattern.

@{b}   SYNOPSIS@{ub}
       asl.getFileWithPattern(PTR TO CHAR, LONG=NIL)

       asl.getFileWithPattern(pattern, taglist)

@{b}   FUNCTION@{ub}
       Opens a file requester that displays the files that match the pattern
       provided.

@{b}   INPUTS@{ub}
       pattern:PTR TO CHAR -- The pattern of the files that should appear in
           the file list. The usual dos.library wildcards are allowed.

       taglist:LONG -- @{"asl" Link "asl/asl()"} tags. See CBM's asl.doc for those.

@{b}   RESULT@{ub}
       PTR TO CHAR -- The chosen file or NIL if the user aborted.

@{b}   NOTES@{ub}
       The attributes lastFileChosen and lastDirChosen are set by this proc.

       Stolen from JRH's rkrm examples.

@{b}   KNOWN BUGS@{ub}
       Tries to add a file name even if no file was chosen. Fixed this bug
       (May 26 1996 Gregor Goldbach).

@{b}   SEE ALSO@{ub}
       @{"asl/asl" Link "asl/asl()"}, CBM's asl.doc, JRH's rkrm examples

@EndNode

@Node "open()" "asl/open"

@{b}   NAME@{ub}
       open() of @{"asl" Link "asl/asl()"} -- Open the asl.library.

@{b}   SYNOPSIS@{ub}
       asl.open()

@{b}   FUNCTION@{ub}
       Open the asl.library. The version to open can be specified in the
       option list you pass to @{"new()" Link "resource/new()"}.

@{b}   EXCEPTION@{ub}
       As with all libraries, the exception "lib" is raised when the opening
       failed. The exceptioninfo contains a @{"string" Link "reqtools/string()"} that tells this.

@{b}   NOTES@{ub}
       The @{"string" Link "reqtools/string()"} may be localized in the future.

@{b}   SEE ALSO@{ub}
       @{"asl" Link "asl/asl()"}

@EndNode

@Node "init()" "reqtools/init"

@{b}   NAME @{ub}
       init() -- Initialization of the object.

@{b}   SYNOPSIS@{ub}
       asl.init()

@{b}   FUNCTION@{ub}
       Copies 'SYS:' to the lastDirChosen attribute.
       Sets the library's name and the version to 0. After that the library
       is opened.

@{b}   SEE ALSO@{ub}
       @{"open()" Link "open()"}
@EndNode

